														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3488273">
									

<p>First of all, I have to say that this tale is amazing. It's definitely my favorite out of all that I've read, and it really deserves more recognition. Second, I've got some questions about how this fits in with the Scarlet King and Sarkic parts of the canon. Was it meant to have any sort of ties to those two entities? Is it implied that the darkness is the Scarlet King? And if these children are the ones creating the anomalies, where does that leave Yaldabaoth? Are they just one conglomerate entity that seeks to destroy our reality? Sorry about all the questions, but the tale was just so interesting and thought provoking that I need to know more</p>

							</div>

								
					
